---
export const label = 'Strategic partnership; punchy, direct';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What if the project doesn\u2019t work out?',
    answer:
      'Every engagement starts with a paid discovery phase. By the time we commit to a full build, we both know exactly what we\u2019re building and why. I don\u2019t take projects I don\u2019t believe in.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How involved do I need to be?',
    answer:
      'You stay in the loop without being in the weeds. I own the technical execution and bring you in for strategic decisions. You\u2019ll always know what\u2019s happening and why\u200a\u2014\u200ain plain language.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How is this different from hiring an agency?',
    answer:
      'At an agency, you\u2019re a ticket in a queue. Here, I\u2019m personally accountable for your product. No account managers, no hand-offs, no layers between you and the person writing the code.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can you handle a bigger build?',
    answer:
      'Yes. I\u2019ve hired and managed teams of developers when the project demanded it. You get the focus of a solo practitioner with the capacity to scale when it matters.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What if something goes wrong?',
    answer:
      'I\u2019ll tell you. Proactively, in plain language, with a plan to fix it. No surprises, no spin. That\u2019s what you\u2019re paying for\u200a\u2014\u200asomeone who treats your product like their own.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Who owns the code?',
    answer:
      'You do. Everything I build is yours\u200a\u2014\u200athe code, the infrastructure, the documentation. If we part ways, you walk away with a product that any competent developer can pick up.',
  },
];
---

<section class="py-16 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold mb-10">
      You might be wondering
    </h2>
    <dl class="space-y-8">
      {
        faqs.map((faq) => (
          <div>
            <dt class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">{faq.question}</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted leading-relaxed">{faq.answer}</dd>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>
